[1] Jordan, 2 new cases - press release 28 Aug 2015
Date: 28 Aug 2015
Source: Jordan News Agency (Petra) [edited]
http://www.petra.gov.jo/Public_News/Nws_NewsDetails.aspx?Site_Id=1&lang=2&NewsID=211364&CatID=13&Type=Home


Jordan reports 2 new corona virus cases
---------------------------------------
Jordan announced that it has registered 16 corona virus infections, since the virus was 1st reported back in 2012.

The Ministry of Health yesterday [27 Aug 2015] announced 2 new cases for 2 males, 78 and 48 years old, that were in direct contact with an infected person at the hospital.

The health ministry said the new cases are under an epidemiological investigation the ministry started for persons who dealt with infected people, adding that one man was in a stable condition, while the other was in critical condition.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[With the addition of these 2 cases, it makes 4 newly confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection reported by Jordan in the past 3 days. The mention that these 2 newly confirmed cases were acquired in the healthcare environment suggests that one or both of the 2 earlier reported cases this week may have been undiagnosed in the healthcare environment for a period of time, without adequate infection control measures. Hopefully the areas of exposure did not involve overcrowded emergency rooms as seen elsewhere, so that it will be relatively easy to interrupt transmission in the affected healthcare facility (or facilities) involved. The addition of these 2 newly confirmed cases raises the number of cases reported in Jordan to 23 -- including those 7 retrospectively confirmed through serologic testing involved in the 1st MERS-CoV outbreak in April 2012 (see MERS-CoV - Eastern Mediterranean (31): Jordan, retro. case ID, WHO, RFI 20130617.1777989).

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Jordan can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3608888,91. - Mod.MPP]

