[2] Jordan, 1 death - media report 28 Aug 2015
Date: 28 Aug 2015
Source: Fulton News [edited]
http://www.newsfultoncounty.com/health/news/288097-jordan-reports-first-coronavirus-death-in-2015


Jordan reports 1st coronavirus death in 2015
--------------------------------------------
- Number of deaths from coronavirus in Jordan up to 7 since 2012

The Jordanian Ministry of Health announced late on Thursday [27 Aug 2015] the death of a 60-year-old male who contracted coronavirus.

Health Ministry spokesman Hatem al-Azrai told Anadolu Agency that "the deceased man had returned to Jordan from Saudi Arabia and was placed in a hospital on Tuesday [25 Aug 2015] because of his bad condition until he died today [Thursday]."

This is Jordan's 1st recorded death as a result of the virus in 2015. Seven people have died from the virus in Jordan since 2012, according to al-Azrai.

The spokesman called on Jordanians who are getting ready to go to Saudi Arabia for the Hajj pilgrimage in September [2015] to be cautious.

On Tuesday [25 Aug 2015], the Saudi health ministry announced the registration of 6 new deaths from the virus, which has left 498 people dead since September 2012.

Also called MERS, the corona disease has been reported in Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Tunisia, Jordan, Egypt and Oman.

The virus, for which no cure currently exists, is known to destroy the lungs and kidneys.

[Byline: Kristoff Saunders]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[If one includes the 7 recovered individuals from the April 2012 ICU outbreak who were diagnosed retrospectively, the reported case fatality rate for MERS-CoV cases would be 30.4 percent. - Mod.MPP]

