[3] Saudi Arabia, 2 new cases - MOH 28 Aug 2015
Date: 28 Aug 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-08-28-001.aspx


As of 12:00 noon today [28 Aug 2015] there have been a total of:
1173 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
502 deaths
606 recoveries and
65 currently active cases including 9 cases of home isolation

In the past 24 hours there have been:
2 newly confirmed cases
0 newly reported deaths
1 newly reported recovery

[reported case fatality rate: 42.8 percent]

Information on newly reported cases (2 cases):
(Both cases reported in Riyadh)
1- A 50 year old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. No known contact with other case(s) in the 14 days preceding onset of illness.

2- A 68 year old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, currently in critical condition. History of contact with other case(s) in the 14 days preceding onset of illness.

Information on newly reported recovery (1 case):
A 41 year old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker from Riyadh. [There was a 41 year old Saudi male from Riyadh reported on 16 and 22 Aug 2015. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours there have been only 2 newly confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection reported. Both cases were from Riyadh, one of whom did not give a history of known contact with other case(s) in the 14 days preceding onset of illness. Looking at cases reported in Riyadh, on 24 Aug 2015, 4 of the 6 newly reported cases (from Riyadh) that day did not give a history of known contact with other case(s), on 22 Aug 2015, 1 out of 7 newly reported cases did not give a history of known contact with other cases and on 21 Aug 2015, 1 out of 6 newly reported cases did not give a history of known contact with other cases. So a question that comes to mind is that with increasing numbers of cases denying known contact with other cases, is there ongoing community transmission of the virus, or are there cases appearing in other healthcare institutions that have not as yet been identified as locations with ongoing MERS-CoV transmission?

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Saudi Arabia can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3608888,131. - Mod.MPP]

